## Auth Hooks — Custom Logic on Auth Events

Auth Hooks let you run custom Postgres functions when specific auth events happen.
You write a PL/pgSQL function, then point Supabase at it.

### Hook types available
| Hook | When it fires | What you can do |
|---|---|---|
| Custom Access Token | Before JWT is issued | Add custom claims to the JWT |
| Send Email | On auth email (confirm, reset, magic link) | Use your own email provider |
| Send SMS | On phone OTP | Use your own SMS provider |
| MFA Verification | On MFA code check | Add custom verification logic |

### Custom Access Token Hook — Add claims to JWT
```sql
-- 1. Create the hook function
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.custom_access_token_hook(event JSONB)
RETURNS JSONB LANGUAGE plpgsql AS $$
DECLARE
  claims JSONB;
  user_role TEXT;
BEGIN
  -- Get user's role from your own table
  SELECT role INTO user_role
  FROM public.profiles
  WHERE id = (event->>'user_id')::UUID;

  -- Get existing claims and add your custom field
  claims := event->'claims';
  claims := jsonb_set(claims, '{user_role}', to_jsonb(COALESCE(user_role, 'user')));
  claims := jsonb_set(claims, '{app_metadata}', '{"source": "rocket"}');

  -- Return modified event
  RETURN jsonb_set(event, '{claims}', claims);
END;
$$;

-- 2. Grant permissions (required)
GRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION public.custom_access_token_hook TO supabase_auth_admin;
REVOKE EXECUTE ON FUNCTION public.custom_access_token_hook FROM authenticated, anon;
```

```
3. Connect in Supabase Dashboard:
   Authentication → Hooks → Custom Access Token → Set function to: public.custom_access_token_hook
```

```typescript
// Now your JWT contains user_role — read it in Next.js
const { data: { session } } = await supabase.auth.getSession()
// Never use getSession() server-side! Only for client-side JWT reading
// For server-side, decode the JWT from getUser():
const { data: { user } } = await supabase.auth.getUser()
const userRole = user?.app_metadata?.user_role
```

### Send Email Hook — Use Resend instead of Supabase emails
```sql
-- Replace Supabase's default email with your own
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.custom_send_email(event JSONB)
RETURNS JSONB LANGUAGE plpgsql AS $$
BEGIN
  -- Call your Edge Function to send the email
  PERFORM net.http_post(
    url := 'https://[PROJECT_REF].functions.supabase.co/send-auth-email',
    headers := jsonb_build_object(
      'Content-Type', 'application/json',
      'Authorization', 'Bearer ' || current_setting('app.service_role_key', true)
    ),
    body := jsonb_build_object(
      'email_type', event->>'email_type',  -- signup, recovery, magic_link, etc.
      'to', event->'email_data'->>'to',
      'token', event->'email_data'->>'token',
      'token_hash', event->'email_data'->>'token_hash',
      'site_url', event->'email_data'->>'site_url'
    )
  );
  RETURN event;
END;
$$;
```

