## Anonymous Sign-Ins

Users can interact with your app before creating an account.
Enable in: Supabase Dashboard → Authentication → Providers → Anonymous sign-ins → Enable.

```typescript
// Sign in anonymously (no email required)
const { data, error } = await supabase.auth.signInAnonymously()
// Creates a real user with is_anonymous: true in auth.users

// Convert anonymous to real user (when they decide to sign up)
const { error } = await supabase.auth.updateUser({ email: 'user@example.com' })
// Sends confirmation email. On confirm, user becomes permanent.

// Or link to OAuth
const { error } = await supabase.auth.linkIdentity({ provider: 'google' })
```

```sql
-- Check if user is anonymous in RLS
CREATE POLICY "anonymous_can_read"
ON public.products FOR SELECT
USING (true);  -- allow anonymous users to browse

CREATE POLICY "only_real_users_can_buy"
ON public.orders FOR INSERT
WITH CHECK (
  (auth.jwt() ->> 'is_anonymous')::BOOLEAN IS NOT TRUE
);
```

