## Column Level Security (CLS)

More granular than RLS — restrict which **columns** users can read, not just rows.

```sql
-- Grant only specific columns to authenticated users
GRANT SELECT (id, name, email, created_at) ON public.profiles TO authenticated;
-- authenticated users CANNOT select phone, stripe_customer_id, internal_notes

-- Grant full read to service role (bypasses both RLS and CLS)
GRANT SELECT ON public.profiles TO service_role;

-- Verify grants
SELECT grantee, privilege_type, column_name
FROM information_schema.column_privileges
WHERE table_name = 'profiles';
```

