## Auth Error Codes Reference

Common errors and what they mean:

| Error Code | Message | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| `invalid_credentials` | Invalid login credentials | Email/password wrong, or email not confirmed |
| `email_not_confirmed` | Email not confirmed | User must click confirmation link |
| `over_email_send_rate_limit` | Too many emails | Wait and retry, or check rate limits |
| `session_not_found` | Session not found | Token expired — user must re-login |
| `user_already_exists` | User already registered | Email already in use — direct to login |
| `weak_password` | Password too weak | Minimum 6 chars by default (configurable) |
| `otp_expired` | OTP expired | Magic link/OTP older than 1 hour — resend |
| `provider_email_needs_verification` | Provider email unverified | OAuth provider email not yet verified |
| `mfa_factor_not_found` | MFA factor not found | factorId is wrong or user unenrolled |
| `mfa_challenge_expired` | MFA challenge expired | Challenge older than 5 minutes — create new one |

```typescript
// Handle auth errors properly
const { data, error } = await supabase.auth.signInWithPassword({ email, password })
if (error) {
  switch (error.code) {
    case 'invalid_credentials':
      return { error: 'Email or password is incorrect' }
    case 'email_not_confirmed':
      return { error: 'Please check your email and confirm your account' }
    case 'over_email_send_rate_limit':
      return { error: 'Too many attempts. Please wait a few minutes.' }
    default:
      return { error: error.message }
  }
}
```

